The last thing I remember was saying goodbye to my loved ones, it was still fresh to my memories. Yet here I am with my other selves, all watching me on his next life. I see an old me, I see a toddler me, and mostly other me's that are my age. The reason how most of the me's my age passed should have been not too different from how I passed away. I had been stabbed in the chest, and I was bleeding out. Fortunately I knew I was dying and I said my proper goodbyes with my family.

The me that we were all watching died differently than I did, but it was done by the same person. He was killed by my best friend, who I had known for years. Only this time not by being stabbed in the chest, but by being shot in the head. Poor other me, he died on the spot and wasn't able to say goodbye.

I had been stabbed in the chest, and I was bleeding out. Fortunately I knew I was dying and I said my proper goodbyes with my family.

The me that we were all watching died differently than I did, but it was done by the same person. He was killed by my best friend, who I had known for years. Only this time not by being stabbed in the chest, but by being shot in the head. Poor other me, he died on the spot and wasn't able to say goodbye.

The other movies of other me's started playing. Some had great endings, some where I grew old and died of old age, some I died of cancer, some I died of a car crash, and some I died of a heart attack. But I couldn't ignore the fact that most of my deaths was done by one person: my best friend. How I died differed each time, but he was always the culprit.

Then I realized why he was doing it. He was jealous of me, he wanted to be the one that was loved by everyone. Right when I was saying goodbye in my death bed, I knew everybody. My family, my friends, my teachers, my neighbors, and even the people I didn't know. They all loved me, and I loved them. My best friend did not like that.

So in all my other lives from these different dimensions I have watched, I have seen the same thing. I wish I could tell my best friend that I love him, and that I forgive him.

The last thing I remember was saying goodbye to my loved ones, it was still fresh to my memories. Yet here I am with my other selves, all watching me on his next life. I see an old me, I see a toddler me, and mostly other me's that are my age. The reason how most of the me's my age passed should have been not too different from how I passed away. I had been stabbed in the chest, and I was bleeding out. Fortunately I knew I was dying and I said my proper goodbyes with my family.

The me that we were all watching died differently than I did, but it was done by the same person. He was killed by my best friend, who I had known for years. Only this time not by being stabbed in the chest, but by being shot in the head. Poor other me, he died on the spot and wasn't able to say goodbye.

The other movies of other me's started playing. Some had great endings, some where I grew old and died of old age, some I died of cancer, some I died of a car crash, and some I died of a heart attack. But I couldn't ignore the fact that most of my deaths was done by one person: my best friend. How I died differed each time, but he was always the culprit.

Then I realized why he was doing it. He was jealous of me, he wanted to be the one that was loved by everyone. Right when I was saying goodbye in my death bed, I knew everybody. My family, my friends, my teachers, my neighbors, and even the people I didn't know. They all loved me, and I loved them. My best friend did not like that.

So in all my other lives from these different dimensions I have watched, I have seen the same thing. I wish I could tell my best friend that I love him, and that I forgive him. I wished that I could tell him that I know he is jealous of me, and that I wish he could be happy.

Then I realized why he was doing it. He was jealous of me, he wanted to be the one that was loved by everyone. Right when I was saying goodbye in my death bed, I knew everybody. My family, my friends, my teachers, my neighbors, and even the people I didn't know. They all loved me, and I loved them. My best friend did not like that.

So in all my other lives from these different dimensions I have watched, I have seen the same thing. I wish I could tell my best friend that I love him, and that I forgive him. I wished that I could tell him that I know he is jealous of me, and that I wish he could be happy. 

My wife, named Amanda, was pregnant with our first child. And I failed to see that my best friend was in love with her. I was too busy with my own life, and I didn't notice that my best friend was slowly being consumed by jealousy.
